summary: SummaryLancome L'Absolu Rouge Cream Lipstick, where intense lip color meets comfort with up to 18 hours of long-lasting comfort.
details: DetailsFeaturesLanc么me's renovated L'Absolu Rouge Cream Lipstick is enriched with 30% moisturizing rose balm and blended with Hyaluronic Acid to provide you with long-lasting comfort and hydration.Available in mutilple luxurious shades, each lipstick has an ultra-creamy texture which glides over the lips and sets to a smudge resistant long-wearing lip color.BenefitsComfortable cream finishContains 30% Rose Balm ExtractHyaluronic Acid & cold pressed oil for hydration throughout the dayUp to 18H of comfortable wearItem 2590317How To UseApply lipstick in a single stroke using the lipstick bulletMake sure lips are hydrated prior to lipstick applicationFor the perfect result, apply lip color to your lips from the center outwardBlot off any excess if required.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Apply lipstick in a single stroke using the lipstick bulletMake sure lips are hydrated prior to lipstick applicationFor the perfect result, apply lip color to your lips from the center outwardBlot off any excess if required.

reviews.headline: Will Continue to buy.
reviews.comments: Love this brand!

reviews.headline: Gorgeous and hydrating
reviews.comments: I love these lipsticks. They are very smooth and pigmented. They glide on effortlessly and have some beautiful colors. They also don't make my perpetually dry prone lips drier. I bought shade French Tea and French Cur. I wanted to try shades a bit different than my usual and I'm very happy with them both. For reference I'm medium deep olive skin tone.

reviews.headline: Feels Amazing
reviews.comments: Highly recommend. Very nourishing and feels great on! My lips feel moisturized for a long time.

reviews.headline: Gorgeous
reviews.comments: I absolutely love this lipstick!  The container, the creaminess and the color are all perfect!  I wouldn't pay full price for it, but I will certainly stock up during the next sale.

reviews.headline: Worth it
reviews.comments: Its a little pricey but the formula is wonderful. Goes on smooth and is very flattering.

reviews.headline: Really wanted to love it BUT not fragrance free
reviews.comments: I used to buy Lancome's color design years ago. Was so disappointed when they discontinued the collection, the colors & price point worked for me. I figured with the 40% off national lipstick week discount, I'd try the step up. I settled on Exotic Orchid. Lovely color but when I got home, I realized it has a fragrance. Unfortunately, I'm sensitive to fragrances. I really don't understand why they'd put a fragrance in the lipstick since it's literally sitting right below your nose. Also, although it has high end packaging, the tube is now so bulky, it doesn't fit into my lipstick holder tray. Never had that issue before. These little things matter.

reviews.headline: Lancome lipstick
reviews.comments: This goes on smoothly and lasts.  No reapplying.

reviews.headline: 326 Coquette is NOT Pink, Ulta
reviews.comments: Ulta has THE WORST shade photos and shade descriptions. I ordered 326 Coquette because it says it's a COOL toned PINK. The photos show a lovely brownish mid-toned pink. So pretty. Wrong. This is a PASTEL ORANGE FROST. This is way too expensive of a lipstick to keep for a pastel orange frost. I will be returning for sure. Love Lancome's lip formula but this shade is not it for me in the least. Ulta needs to do better on shade descriptions and photos.

reviews.headline: Love Lanc么me Lippies
reviews.comments: I've worn Lanc么me creme lipsticks for a long time. Love them. My fave color now is Rose Cocktail. A nice, icey pink.

reviews.headline: i like it
reviews.comments: the color is very beautiful in person. when i swatched it on my hand i was unsure but it looks great. wonderful formula, a little noticeable but definitely not annoying. it doesn't move around on the lips. buildable coverage, but pigmented!

reviews.headline: Beautiful
reviews.comments: This is a stunning red. I love it ss a statement with just some liner, mascara and blush. No need for anything else, this red speaks for itself. Powerful, confident and so Wow in a tube!

reviews.headline: I will buy this product again
reviews.comments: I have been using this lipstick for several years and I love it. The color seems to go with almost everything

reviews.headline: Beautiful color
reviews.comments: Velvety and smooth. Usually not a fan of matte lipstick, but this one is great!!

reviews.headline: LOVE!
reviews.comments: I LOVE my new Lancome #112 lipstick!  I bought it on sale + used an Ulta's $20 off coupon, and paid under $15.00.  I love the color, smell, and smooth texture.  It feels like butter.  It's a pretty coral color that can be used throughout the year.

reviews.headline: I will definitely buy again!
reviews.comments: This shade is beautiful. This is a very flattering lipstick. My lips look plump and moisturized. Not to mention the case is very cool! I will buy more colors.

reviews.headline: I would buy this product again.
reviews.comments: I'm a Lanc么me girl. I've used their products for over 40 years!  Love them!!

reviews.headline: Perfect shade
reviews.comments: This has been my favorite shade for years.  Lancome makes such great products!

reviews.headline: Lancome lipstick
reviews.comments: Wearing this for years,they changed the name that I finally figured it out myself because lancome reps didn't know !!!

reviews.headline: Disappointed
reviews.comments: Does not cover lip evenly. Feathers badly. Waste of money.

reviews.headline: I buy this lipstick again and again!
reviews.comments: My favorite red lipstick.  I love these lipsticks!  They do not dry out my lips and are long lasting.

faceoff_positive.comments: I purchased 4 different colors of this lipstick line and I am so happy for this purchased. The product are just so perfect for me - the application is so perfect and I am so in love of this product line. Very easy to apply and the colors lasts longer. I hope that this will not change in its production components - it is hard to love something's and then get discontinued. Giving it a million stars!
faceoff_positive.headline: Worthy of a million stars

faceoff_negative.comments: I tried 3 colors. All seem drier than the previous reincarnations of the Rouge Absolue line. The scent is nice - soft and nit overpowering. However, I am particularly disappointed with Mademoiselle Amanda color - it does not stay on at all. I also do not care for plastic packaging.
faceoff_negative.headline: Not what I'd expect from my Lancome
